Hello,

At the recent Berlin 4 conference I made mention=20
of the CODATA SADC meeting's executive summary=20
and recommendations which were awaiting official=20
release. That report is now officially released=20
and available, and is important since
    * apart from its being a CODATA document in=20
collaboration with the South African National=20
Research Foundation and any sway that that would hold
    * it arises from the Southern hemisphere
    * makes important recommendations vis-a-vis=20
mandated access to data and information.
    * and speaks of policy interventions by=20
funders in their requiring self-archiving
I've tried to access this final document so as to=20
verify that the version I have of a month ago=20
corresponds to this officially released one, but=20
the web site had some tech diffculties. In the=20
meantime see key excerpts as blogged at
